  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@1294 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.5. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc p2y/Vnl_driver.F config/configure.ac xc_functionals/spin_density.F wf_and_fft/fft_setup.F pol_function/Dipole_dip_dot_field.F modules/mod_vec_operate.F ypp/RT_fix_symmetries.F ypp/RT_build_spin_sop.F

   - [SPIN SOP] spin_sop (presently used only in RT_fix_symm) for the non_collinear case fixed and tested
   - [RT_fix_symm] WFs are now rotated in g-space without the FFT. Also the g-vector-shells for each wf are rotated. These two changes enable to have a closed shell for the rotated  wf centered on the right
     k-point.
     Thus the  "PWscf structure" is preserved. No changes for abinit wfs.

  [BUG] in the collinear case (n_sp_pol=2) the spin density is assumed to be always along the z direction and must not be rotated with the spatial symmetries.

  Patch sent by: Davide


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@1288 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

