.F io/variables_BS.F io/io_elemental.F io/ioDB1.F io/io_HF_and_locXC.F io/ioX.F io/variables_X.F io/ioGROT.F io/ioWF.F io/ioBSS_invert.F io/ver_is_gt_or_eq.F io/IO_and_Messaging_switch.F io/ioQP.F io/ioQINDX.F io/io_header.F io/ioRIM.F io/ioCOL_CUT.F io/ioBSS_Haydock.F io/Fragments_Synchronize.F io/ioBSS_diago.F io/ioKB_PP.F io/ioE_RIM.F io/.objects io/ioDB1_reload.F io/io_bulk.F io/io_DIPOLES.F io/io_Vnl.F io/IO_Setup.F io/variables_DIPOLES.F io/Fragments_Restart.F modules/mod_electrons.F modules/mod_logo.F modules/mod_frequency.F modules/mod_units.F modules/mod_zeros.F modules/mod_BS.F modules/mod_TDDFT.F modules/mod_R_lattice.F modules/mod_fields.F modules/mod_memory.F modules/mod_functions.F modules/mod_libxc_int.F modules/mod_wave_func.F modules/mod_drivers.F modules/mod_xc_functionals.F modules/mod_ACFDT.F modules/mod_fragments.F modules/mod_timing.F modules/mod_X_output.F modules/mod_vec_operate.F modules/mod_pseudo.F modules/std_presets.F modules/mod_par_indexes.F modules/mod_stderr.F modules/mod_pars.F modules/mod_par_proc.F modules/mod_IO.F modules/mod_X.F modules/mod_com.F modules/mod_FFT.F modules/mod_QP.F modules/mod_wrapper.F modules/mod_matrix_operate.F modules/.objects modules/mod_D_lattice.F modules/mod_global_XC.F modules/mod_collision.F bse/K_Haydock.F bse/K_exchange.F bse/K_scattering.F bse/K_filling.F bse/K_BSmat_by_V.F bse/.objects bse/K_driver.F bse/K_diagonalization.F bse/K_eh_setup.F bse/K_inversion.F bse/K_solvers.F bse/K_eps_interpolate.F bse/K_output_file.F bse/K.F ypp/ypp_init.F ypp/plot_xcrysden.F ypp/electrons_dos_and_charge.F ypp/qpdb_setup.F ypp/mod_YPP.F ypp/excitons_driver.F ypp/electrons_charge.F ypp/qpdb_init.F ypp/electrons_driver.F ypp/plot_cube.F ypp/ypp_i.F ypp/excitons_sort_and_report.F ypp/k_grids.F ypp/.objects ypp/plot_gnuplot.F ypp/plot_check_and_launch.F ypp/k_random.F ypp/ypp_init_load.F driver/p2y.h driver/a2y.h driver/editor.h.in driver/codever.h.in driver/e2y.h driver/yambo_driver.F driver/driver.c driver/yambo.h driver/ypp.h sbin/make_message.pl.in sbin/make_makefile.sh.in sbin/objects_debug.sh.in

  *** GLOBAL UPDATE from revision 949 to revision 1004 ***

  Bugs:
  - Small bug fix in O_driver for out-of-the BZ calculations (PJ + Claudio)
  - Fixed flags and compilation problems
  - Memory leaks due to nullify of pointers fixed
  - Small bug in QP report
  - Bug searching the nearest k-point without symmetries, be_carefull=.FALSE (Davide)
  - In k_lattice. This is an old issue related to the search of the unit vectors of the BZ grid. I already had changed this part in 2010 but,
    apparently, it does not work always, like in the surface case of the Fantastic Dimensions tutorial. Therefore I decided to merge the old
    and new method in a new procedure that, hopefully, will work always.

  Additions:
  - Added a routine (variables_X) to handle the description strings of the response function
  - ERIM for the BSE added
  - Possibility to link FFT different from FFTW for example MKL one
    see http://www.yambo-code.org/doc/compiling.php

  Changes:
  - GLOBAL COPYRIGHT YEAR RANGE change
  - Changed the singer "Armstrong" for the unit "Angstroms" (Davide)
  - Typos in Bethe-Salpter output (Davide)
  - Partial Fix of optical calculations using shifted grids. Eps0 calculated with the shifted grids agree with the calculation with
    the non-local part of the pseudo. There is still  a large prefactor (~70) I could not find the reason of. Also the
    generation of the grids by ypp has been changed.
    *** this piece of code is still to test and improve ***


  Patch sent by: Andrea


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@1005 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

