  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@954 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.4. [Andrea Marini]

  *  qp/QP_ppa_cohsex.F common/OCCUPATIONS_Fermi.F pol_function/X_os.F pol_function/O_kerr.F pol_function/.objects pol_function/O_kerr_shadow.F real_time/RT_elph_Kernel.F real_time/RT_Collision.F real_time/RT_G_retarded.F real_time/RT_initialize.F real_time/RT_generalized_KBA.F io/io_SC_components.F modules/mod_real_time.F ChangeLog

  Bugs:
  - [RT] In RT_G_retarded.F caused by the change of sign of the interpolated lifetime

  Additions:
  - [RT] S_matrix added in view of a possible iterative solution of the time evolution in presence of a BK kernel
    with memory. Iterative solution based on a simlpe ansatz on the G_retarded time-dependence. Full time
    dependence of G_lesser kept to perform tests.
  - [RT] Working version of the el-ph kernel of the BKE (RT_elph_Kernel.F).
    Routine checked against simple model using IP dynamics and G_lesser frozen.
    Time dependence seems ok. Not sure about +/- and I flowing around.
  - [RT] Working version of the Generaized Baym-Kadanoff Ansatz routine. Occupation
    factors fixed and both possible time-orderings coded.
  - [RT] Negative max_rt_steps_disk gives no I/O at all.

  Changes:
  - [RT] Added different names of G_lesser databases written at different times.
  - ChangeLog updated
  - [KERR] New implementation of yambo_kerr (at IP level) finalized and checked against old implementation on Iron.
    Fixed problems with the Drude term and the computation of the kerr parameters inside yambo.
    There is still a difference in the computation of the off-diagonal part of epsilon. The new results seems closer
    to reference theoretical and experimental data. More tests are needed. (Davide)

  Patch sent by: Andrea & Davide


