- Wrong condition in G_shells_finder. [Andrea Marini]

  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@945 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.4. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/configure.ac qp_ctl/OCCUPATIONS_IO_and_interpolate.F setup/setup.F setup/G_shells_finder.F setup/eval_minus_G.F real_time/RT_driver.F real_time/RT_observables.F real_time/RT_start_and_restart.F sc/SC_add_XC.F sc/SC_driver.F io/io_SC_components.F modules/mod_real_time.F modules/std_presets.F modules/mod_SC.F ypp/RT_databases.F

  *** DEBUG revision. Under major maintenance ***

  Bugs:
  - eval_minus_G() was called BEFORE G_shells_finder() leading to a seg. fault.
  - When the inversion symmetry is not included the shells are not properly closed. This induces
    a consequent seg. fault. in the BSE calculation WITH coupling.

  Changes:
  - [RT] Added time index to G_lesser.

  Patch sent by: Andrea


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@944 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

