  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@934 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.4. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/configure.ac qp/QP_ppa_cohsex.F qp_ctl/OCCUPATIONS_IO_and_interpolate.F setup/setup.F setup/.objects setup/eval_minus_G.F real_time/RT_driver.F real_time/RT_initialize.F real_time/RT_databases_IO.F real_time/RT_Rabi_Function.F real_time/RT_start_and_restart.F modules/mod_R_lattice.F modules/mod_stderr.F bse/K_DISTRIBUTED.F bse/K_driver.F bse/K_inversion.F bse/K.F ypp/k_random.F

  Bugs:
  - In QP_ppa_cohsex wrong number of elements in the live_timing call. This bug was already spotted in previous commits. Therefore
    this new bug-fix must be checked carefully.
  - [RT] I have changed again the definition of it_start to the previous overwritting the previous commit changes. I have
    added a comment to explain the motivation. Accordingly to fix the restart RT_databases_IO has been changed.
  - [YPP] The RIM k-points was failing in the case of a different number of symmetries between the ground state
    calculation and the Yambo databases. Fixed.

  Additions:
  - eval_minus_G.F. In order to do BSE calculations with fractional occupations the coupling is necessary. Before this
    commit, however, non-resonant calculations were possibile only by using the Time-Reversal. This condition has been
    removed by introducing a table to find the indexes of the -G vectors.

  Changes:
  - [RT,SC] OCCUPATIONS_IO_and_interpolate.F: Added RIM support. More informations are now written in the report.

  Patch sent by: Andrea


