- Version 3.2.4. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/configure.ac qp/QP_driver.F qp/XCo_driver.F qp/QP_of.F qp/QP_Green_Function.F qp/QP_descriptions.F qp/QP_report_and_write.F qp/QP_real_axis.F qp/ELPH_Sigma_c.F qp/QP_newton.F qp/ELPH_Hamiltonian.F qp/QP_secant.F qp/QP_ppa_cohsex.F acfdt/acfdt_tot_energy.F qp_ctl/QP_apply_global_stretch.F qp_ctl/mod_QP_CTL.F ras/write_eps_tensor.F ras/io_ostnts_cut.F ras/reels_spectrum.F ras/write_reelsdiff.F ras/io_slab_eps.F ras/extract_eps_surf.F ras/rasdriver.F ras/ras_spectrum.F common/OCCUPATIONS_Extend.F common/OCCUPATIONS_Fermi.F parser/ps_convert.F parser/init_convert.F pol_function/O_eels.F pol_function/X_os.F pol_function/O_driver.F pol_function/X_GreenF_remap.F interface/init.F setup/QP_state_table_setup.F ras_reels_mods/mod_eels_gvec.F ras_reels_mods/mod_eels_kinematics.F ras_reels_mods/mod_bulkeps.F ras_reels_mods/mod_eels_scattering.F ras_reels_mods/mod_eels_qpt.F ras_reels_mods/mod_convolute.F ras_reels_mods/reels_presets.F ras_reels_mods/mod_eels_detector.F ras_reels_mods/mod_eels_wgrid.F ras_reels_mods/mod_loss_module.F ras_reels_mods/mod_ras.F ras_reels_mods/ras_presets.F real_time/RT_Field_Commensurable_Frequencies.F real_time/RT_Collision.F real_time/RT_initialize.F real_time/RT_init_two_levels.F real_time/RT_observables.F real_time/RT_TwoL_Glesser.F real_time/RT_three_levels.F real_time/RT_Fluence.F real_time/RT_update.F real_time/RT_Rabi_Function.F real_time/RT_start_and_restart.F real_time/RT_two_levels.F communicate/REPORT_Energies.F communicate/REPORT_Occupations.F sc/XC_switch.F sc/SC_start_and_restart.F sc/SC_driver.F sc/MAG_A_phase.F sc/SC_History.F io/variables_SC.F io/ioX.F io/ioBSS_invert.F io/ioBS_Fxc.F io/variables_BS.F io/ioDB1.F io/io_header.F io/variables_DIPOLES.F modules/mod_frequency.F modules/mod_units.F modules/mod_fields.F modules/std_presets.F modules/mod_X.F modules/mod_QP.F bse/K_output_file.F reels/average_epsm1_q.F reels/epsinv.F reels/reelsdriver.F reels/calc_loss_function.F reels/write_output.F ypp/ypp_init.F ypp/RT_split_Polarization.F ypp/RT_X_effective.F ypp/plot_xcrysden.F ypp/reels_ypp.F ypp/RT_coefficients_Inversion.F ypp/RT_initialize.F ypp/ELPH_eliashberg_dos.F ypp/ras_trans_ypp.F ypp/RT_X_qssin.F ypp/electrons_dos_and_charge.F ypp/ELPH_databases.F ypp/RT_X_LRR_real_field.F ypp/ELPH_general_gFsq.F ypp/qpdb_setup.F ypp/excitons_driver.F ypp/ELPH_excitonic_gkkp.F ypp/qpdb_init.F ypp/ras_generate_epsdb.F ypp/ras_ypp.F ypp/excitons_sort_and_report.F ypp/plot_gnuplot.F ypp/ELPH_atomic_amplitude.F ypp/k_random.F

  *** MAJOR UPDATE ***

  Changes:
  -  I have GLOBALLY renamed the unit convertion factors following a pre-estabilished
     format: U = U2P * P

     So, for example,

      1 Hartree = 27.21 eV => AU2EV = 27.21
      1 Bohr = 0.53 A      => AU2ARM= 0.53

     and so on.

     These changes have particularly affected the units of the electromagnetic fields (electric field,
     field intensity, Poynting vector and so on). The correctness of these choices has been verified
     by testing that, given a cartain intensity in kW/cm^2, the same electric field (in V/m) is obtained
     using the expression of the Poynting in the S.I., in the C.G.S and in the A.U.
     These values, moreover, quite well agree with the numbers given in the table D.1 of "Nonlinear optics",
     R.W. Boyd, 3rd edition.

     With respect to the previous revisions these changes have dramatically reduced the strength of the
     electric field. I trace back this change in a POSSIBLY wrong definition of the Poynting vector and
     of the convertion factor between kW/cm^2 and AU.

  Patch sent by: Andrea


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@926 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Small bug in OCCUPATIONS_IO_and_interpolate fixed. [Andrea Marini]

  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@925 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.4. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/configure.ac qp/QP_newton.F qp_ctl/mod_QP_CTL.F qp_ctl/.objects qp_ctl/OCCUPATIONS_IO_and_interpolate.F bz_ops/k_the_nearest.F interface/QP_ctl_load.F interface/init_load.F interface/QP_ctl_switch.F interface/init.F setup/QP_external_corrections.F setup/setup.F real_time/RT_output.F real_time/.objects real_time/RT_databases_IO.F real_time/RT_Fluence.F real_time/RT_start_and_restart.F io/variables_SC.F io/io_SC_components.F modules/mod_real_time.F modules/mod_fields.F modules/std_presets.F modules/mod_SC.F modules/mod_QP.F bse/K_driver.F ypp/ypp_init.F ypp/mod_YPP.F ypp/ypp_init_load.F ypp/electrons_dos_and_charge.F ypp/RT_X_LRR_real_field.F ypp/electrons_driver.F ypp/excitons_sort_and_report.F ypp/.objects driver/ypp.h

  Bugs:
  - [RT] Factor 10 spotted by Myrta fixed in RT_Fluence

  Additions:
  - [RT,SC] OCCUPATIONS_IO_and_interpolate.F: This routine stores on a DB the time-dependent occupations
    that can be read and interpolated by the same routine when called by yambo_sc. In this case the occupations
    act as "QP-related" correction allowing post linear-response/GW calculations out-of-the-equilibrium
  - [RT,SC,YPP_RT] Added occupations related variables to fix a loading time and (in the case of ypp_rt) a time step
    used to plot the DOS
  - [YPP,YPP_RT] electrons_dos_and_charge.F: moved in this routine the calculation of the DOS and of the charge
    density. When time-dependent occupations are read teh output is a 3D plot (Energy,Time,DOS).
  - [YPP,YPP_RT] Added several input variables to ypp in order to have a fine control of the DOS calculation

  Changes:
  - Numerical input variable of QP_apply changed in character

  Patch sent by: Andrea


