  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@762 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.4. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/configure.ac qp/ELPH_Sigma_c.F coulomb/rim_spherical.F coulomb/.objects coulomb/col_driver.F interface/init.F real_time/RT_driver.F real_time/RT_output.F real_time/RT_initialize.F real_time/RT_init_two_levels.F real_time/RT_TwoL_Glesser.F real_time/.objects real_time/RT_databases_IO.F real_time/RT_Integrator.F real_time/RT_TwoL_Polarization.F real_time/RT_start_and_restart.F real_time/RT_two_levels.F io/io_SC_components.F modules/mod_real_time.F modules/mod_fields.F modules/std_presets.F ypp/ypp_init.F ypp/RT_databases.F ypp/RT_init_X_one.F ypp/mod_YPP.F ypp/RT_fix_symmetries.F ypp/RT_X_one.F

  Bugs:
  - [RT] In RT_driver mat_dia_inv was called also when RT_diagonalization_steps=0

  Additions:
  - [ELPH] Added simple spherical implementation of the RIM to weight
    correctly the contribution near the gamma-point
  - [RT] Added the 2levels P(t) in RT. This is calculated on-the-fly and it is not restricted
    to the linear response regime. It yields the exact non-interacting P(t) at low-fields.
  - [YPP_RT] Added the possiblity to use the 2levels P(t) to calculate the non-interacting
    eps(w)
  - [RT] i_Pump, i_Probe and a logical to say if the two-levels P(t) is available is now written
    in the DBs.

  Changes:
  - [RT] ndb.RT_current => ndb.RT_J_and_P

  Patch sent by: Andrea


