  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@682 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.3. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/configure.ac interface/init_load.F interface/init.F io/Fragments_Restart.F io/Fragments_Synchronize.F modules/mod_IO.F bse/K_filling.F bse/K.F driver/a2y.h driver/c2y.h driver/e2y.h driver/yambo.h driver/ypp.h driver/p2y.h driver/driver.c

  Bugs:
  - [CPMD] Removed bug in c2y when treating big databases (fragmentation) (Daniele)
  - [GPL] Missing construction of BS table in ypp when the BSE coupling is switched on (Daniele)
  - Wrong MPI initialization when -S option is used. To avoid future confusion I added to *ALL* .h files that
    define the command line structure an integer to decide whether or not that variable is compatible with a
    parallel run of the driver.
  - Wrong definition of the restart files in the case of a fragmented BS database. Now the restart file has been changed to be
    the same in case of fragmented/non-fragmented databases.
    *** Still to check the fragments syncronization in distributed runs ***
  - Wrong checks in K.F and K_filling.F to restart the loop using the fragments.
  - [ELPH] Small problem compiling with gfortran in qp/ELPH_Hamiltonian.F (Elena)
  - Wrong boundary conditions in ypp fixed. Removed discontinuity observed at the cell boundaries (Davide)

  Patch sent by: Andrea, Daniele, Davide & Elena


