- Version 3.2.2. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc int_modules/mod_dftxc2libxc.F int_modules/.objects int_modules/mod_xc2y.F int_modules/mod_com2y.F p2y/p2y_db1.F p2y/mod_p2y.F a2y/a2y_db1.F config/configure.ac xc_functionals/XC_potential_driver.F xc_functionals/xc_lda_driver.F xc_functionals/XC_libxc_driver.F xc_functionals/libxc_int.F xc_functionals/.objects qp/XCo_local.F acfdt/acfdt_tot_energy.F real_time/RT_Energy.F real_time/RT_Collision.F real_time/RT_start_and_restart.F real_time/RT_init_vecpot.F real_time/RT_two_levels.F sc/SC_add_XC.F tddft/tddft_alda_g_space.F io/ioDB1.F modules/mod_real_time.F modules/mod_libxc_int.F modules/mod_xc_functionals.F modules/.objects modules/mod_global_XC.F bse/K_BSload.F bse/K.F

  Additions:
  - xc_functionals/XC_potential_driver.F, see Changes
  - modules/mod_libxc_int.F, see changes
  - int_modules/mod_xc2y.F: this module should contain all
    convertion between xc conventions in the DFT code and the one in yambo.
    For the moment it contains utilities for xc from abinit and fron abinit linked to LIBXC. Everything is restricted to LDA.

  Changes:
  - The interface to libxc has been changed to localize it and to ensure compability. Most of the files are reverted to their pre-LIBXC status
    (for what concern LIBXC use) and the interface to libxc is contained in xc_functionals/XC_potential_driver.F (to be used
    instead of the xc_lda_driver, the call to xc_lda_driver have been changed all along the code).
    The calls to LIBXC are done by xc_functionals/libxc_int.F using modules/mod_libxc_int.F

  Patch sent by: Myrta


