  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@533 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.1. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc int_modules/mod_com2y.F config/configure.ac ypp/ypp_init.F ypp/RT_fix_symmetries.F ypp/ypp_init_load.F driver/p2y.h driver/a2y.h

  Bugs:
  - In interfaces/int_modules/mod_com2y.F when TR inversion was removed in system
    without spatial inversion
  - In ypp/RT_fix_symmetries.F in case of a system without spatial inversion (*** BUG
    POTENTIALLY SEVERE ***)

  Additions:
  - Option to remove only Time Reversal in ypp_rt

  Changes:
  - To avoid confusion in the use of the interfaces I have:
      * removed "Force no symmetries" flag in a2y/p2y
      * renamed the "Force no TR symmetry" in "Force use of spatial Inv. instead of Time Rev."
    this to make clear that only ypp_rt can modify the total number of symmetries. The interfaces
    can only interpret the time reversal as a spatial inversion when possible.

  Patch sent by: Andrea


