  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@514 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.1. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/configure.ac bz_ops/k_lattice.F

  Bugs:
  - In k_lattice.F wrong estimation of K lattice dim. This bug was introduced in rev. 424
    where I re-wrote a part of k_lattice and it was caused by the assumption that
    k_grid_borders(:,1)< 0 and  k_grid_borders(:,2)>0 in any case. As Myrta pointed out
    this is not true for the 2D sampling of the Si surface we use as tutorial.
    The bug fix is easy and harmless, and it should work only in the above case.

  Patch sent by: Andrea


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@513 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.1. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/acx.m4 config/acx_cpp.m4 config/configure.ac xc_functionals/el_magnetization.F interface/init_load.F interface/init.F setup/check_periodic_directions.F communicate/fermi_msg.F sc/RT_driver.F sc/SC_common_build_Ho.F io/load_RHO_VX_RHO.F io/.objects modules/mod_timing.F modules/mod_oscillators_CACHE.F modules/mod_magnetic.F

  Changes:
   -[RT] load_RHO_VX_RHO.F moved in libio.a (Claudio)
  - Fixed definition (and dimensions) for the average el_mag.
    Now this is the density of magnetization for periodic systems while it is the total
    magnetization for isolated systems. For 1D and 2D systems it is the linear density and
    the surface density of magnetization respectively.   (Davide)

  Additions:
   - build_os=apple added in acx.m4 and acx_cpp.m4  (Claudio)
   - time function for MacOsX added in mod_timing.F (Myrta)

  Bugs:
   - bug in mod_timing.F calling igethname() (Myrta)
   -[SC] in SC_common_build_Ho.F Ho was not set to zero for non magnetic case (Claudio)

  Patch sent by: Claudio, Myrta & Davide


