  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@494 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.1. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc e2y/e2y_i.F p2y/p2y_i.F a2y/a2y_i.F config/Makefile.in config/configure.ac parser/ps_convert.F parser/init_convert.F parser/mod_itm.F wf_and_fft/WF_derivative.F wf_and_fft/wf_load.F interface/init_load.F interface/init.F sc/MAG_common_build_A.F sc/XC_switch.F sc/SC_driver.F sc/SC_check_symmetries.F sc/.objects sc/MAG_Hamiltonian.F io/io_SC_components.F io/IO_mute.F modules/mod_memory.F modules/mod_wave_func.F modules/std_presets.F modules/mod_magnetic.F modules/mod_global_XC.F ypp/ypp_init.F ypp/mod_YPP.F ypp/RT_fix_symmetries.F ypp/electrons_angular_momentum.F ypp/ypp_init_load.F driver/driver.c driver/ypp.h sbin/make_makefile.sh.in

  Bugs:
  - Small bug in double prec compilation fixed in interfaces.

  Additions:
  - Added angle unit (degrees and radians)

  Changes:
  - wf_load changed in order to keep wf allocated in case of k-by-k I/O
  - Implemented the possibility of a magnetic field oriented in any direction
  - Now there are 4 gauges: SYMM, and J_ASYMM with J=X,Y,Z. The asymmetric gauge removes the vector
    potential which grows in the J direction thanks to the generators \Lambda=0.5*Bo*jk with j,k=xyz
    The generator used depends on the gauge choosen
  - In the input the magnetic field has to be specified in polar coordinates, MAG_B, MAG_thata, MAG_psi
  - Changed the subroutine RT_ypp_fix_symm in order to check symmetries even for magnetic fields not along z
  - In the I/O now yambo_magnetic writes also the angles of the of magnetic field orientation
  - Changed ypp_magnetic: now is able to compute <L_j> and <M_j> for j=x,y,z, according to how the magnetic
    field is oriented
  - Pauli magnetism is done now with the direction of the spin aligned with the B-direction, this is always
    possible if the system has not a preferred direction. Just warning that in this case what is called
    \sigma_z is actualli along the B direction!
    If a system has a praferred spin direction then Pauli magnetism would lead to a non-collinear Hamiltonian.

  Patch sent by: Davide (and Andrea for a general restyling)


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@493 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Added Green Function support to BSE inversion. [Andrea Marini]

  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@492 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.1. [Andrea Marini]

