  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@411 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.1. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc p2y/qexml_v3.2.F p2y/p2y_db1.F p2y/p2y_i.F p2y/mod_p2y.F a2y/a2y_db1.F config/Makefile.in config/netcdf_f90.m4 config/configure.ac qp/QP_elph.F qp_ctl/mod_QP_CTL.F qp_ctl/.objects qp_ctl/.objects_gpl common/fermi_level_test_1.F common/.objects common/.objects_gpl common/crystal_lattice.F common/fermi_level.F bz_ops/k_lattice_test_1.F bz_ops/k_lattice.F interface/setup_test_1.F interface/setup.F interface/.objects interface/.objects_gpl communicate/report_energies.F modules/std_presets.F modules/mod_com.F modules/mod_D_lattice.F bse/K_scattering.F bse/K_diagonalization.F ypp/ypp_init.F + ypp/elph_general_gFsq.F ypp/mod_YPP.F ypp/k_analyze.F ypp/ypp_i.F ypp/BZ_RIM.F ypp/.objects ypp/.objects_gpl ypp/ypp_init_load.F ypp/k_special.F driver/a2y.h driver/e2y.h driver/f2y.h driver/yambo.h driver/ypp.h driver/yambo.h_gpl driver/p2y.h driver/ypp.h_gpl driver/driver.c

  Bugs:
  - Bug in QP_elph in case of negative phonon frequencies away from gamma point.

  Additions:
  - crystal_lattice.F added. Unit cell kind (FCC,BCC,HCP and CUB) detected.
  - p2y now reads correctly the PW xc functional.
  - a2y and p2y interfaces use crystal_lattice.F to try to define
    more correctly alat(:) values.
  - new msg_deliver subroutine. Usefull to (post) edit the formatted strings
    created by msg interface.

  Changes:
  - whole qp_ctl added to GPL distro.
  - fermi_level replaced with fermi_level_test_1 containing a more
    efficient quest for the Fermi level (2 TEST)
  - k_lattice replaced with k_lattice_test_1. Comment follows:
    ! Andrea 31/03/2009. Bug pointed out by a user.
    !
    ! writing this routine I assumed that a subgroup of the
    ! k-points constituets a uniform grid .
    ! Of course this is not true if you pick up gamma plus
    ! a point exactly on the BZ border. As a first work around
    ! I extended the k-grid using a certain number of
    ! RL vectors shells. (passed via G_shell)
  - setup.F replaced with setup_test_1. Added calls to crystal_lattice
    and to new form of k_lattice.
  - changed format of "ypp -k". Added "ypp -k h" (k_special.F) to view high symmetry points
    consistent with the unit cell detected by crystal_lattice. Added
    option to create paths (band structure)
  - added declarations in .h files to avoid warning messages during compilation
    of driver.c.

  Patch sent by: Andrea


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@410 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.1. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/configure.ac qp/QP_W2Sc.F modules/mod_BS_doubles.F bse/K_doubles_degeneracy.F bse/K_doubles_diagonalization.F bse/K_doubles.F bse/K_fixed_point.F bse/.objects bse/K_diagonalization.F bse/K_inversion.F bse/K_doubles_mount.F bse/K.F

  Bugs:
  - qp/QP_W2Sc.F
    Inverted the sign of the i\eta factors in the denominator of the QP Green functions
    according to the expression for the T-ordered Green function:
    G=\frac{1}{\omega-\epsilon_i+i\eta sign(\epsilon-\mu)}

  - [DOUBLES] bse/K_doubles.F
    Fixed sign error for some of the elements of the doubles kernel

  - [DOUBLES] bse/K.F
    Added a deallocation line so that the compiled yambo_doubles works even if
    one does a standard computation (i.e.: a static BSE) with the coupling

  - [DOUBLES] bse/k_inversion.F
    Added the BS_mat_static matrix so that in the loop over frequency the doubles kernel
    is correctly add before the inversion and then subtracted after the inversion for
    each frequency.

  Additions:
  - [DOUBLES] bse/K_doubles_degeneracy.F
    Fake subroutine. Presently it does nothing

  - [DOUBLES] bse/K_doubles_diagonalization.F
    Subroutine called by bse/K_diagonalization.F
    Solve the fixed point problem and gives as outup the eigenvales and the eigenvectors.
    In particular the solution of the fixed point equation for each eigenvalue of the
    frequency dependent BS_mat is solved calling the subroutine bse/K_fixed_point.F

  - [DOUBLES] bse/K_fixed_point.F
    Subroutine called by bse/K_doubles_diagonalization.F
    Solve the equation $E_I(\omega)-\omega=0$ for I=1,BS_K_dim


  Changes:
  - [DOUBLES] modules/mod_BS_doubles.F
    Added the following tables used by the subroutine K_doubles_fixed.F _point:
    integer     , allocatable ::  BS_table_fixed_E(:,:)
    integer     , allocatable ::  tab_poles2iw(:)
    Added the following tables in preparation for the subroutin K_doubles_degeneracy.F:
    presently this is a fake subroutins which does nothing
    integer     , allocatable ::  tab_check2icv_zero(:),degeneracy_zero(:)
    integer     , allocatable ::  change(:,:), inv_change(:,:), tab_poles2iw(:)
    Added the following vector for a possible static approximation to be done in
    the code for part of the doubles kernel:
    integer     , allocatable ::  static_approx(:)
    Added the matrix which collects the eigenvectors (both the singles and the doubles part)
    of the "fixed point diagonalization":
    complex(SP) , allocatable ::  Eigen_singles(:,:),Eigen_doubles(:,:)

  - [DOUBLES] bse/K_doubles.F
    Inserted code for a possible static approximation in the doubles kernel and refined comments

  - [DOUBLES] bse/.objects
    Added files: K_fixed_point.o K_doubles_diagonalization.o K_doubles_degeneracy.o

  - [DOUBLES] bse/K_diagonalization.F
    Added: call to K_doubles_diagonalization.F, lines for modules needed to get the output from
    K_doubles_diagonalization.F .
    Finally added some lines needed to compute the residues after the "fixed point diagonalization"
    as we obtain a different number of solution respect to the static one, so BS_R has to be
    allocated with a a different dimension.

  - [DOUBLES] bse/K.F
    Added lines so that the code restarting from the doubles database works in the same way
    as if it start from scratch.

  - [DOUBLES] bse/k_inversion.F
    Modified the code so that yambo_doubles always performs the ful inversion, skipping the perturbative
    inversion

  - [DOUBLES] bse/K_doubles/mount.F
    Added extensive comments and modification for testing pourpose: it's possible to switch from the
    "whole kernel" construction to the "diagrams by diagrams contruction" (so that one can turn on and off
    the contribution from different diagrams separately). Finally added code for a possible static approximation
    to part of the kernel.

  Patch sent by: Davide


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@408 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

