- Small bug in ypp/BZ_RIM.F fixed. [Andrea Marini]

  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@360 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.2.1. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure include/version.inc config/Makefile.in config/Makefile.in_gpl config/acx_cpp.m4 config/configure.ac lib/slatec/dqwgtf.f lib/slatec/d1mach.f lib/slatec/polfit.f lib/slatec/dbesi0.f lib/slatec/dbsi1e.f lib/slatec/dbesk1.f lib/slatec/dbsk1e.f lib/slatec/dqag.f lib/slatec/dqawoe.f lib/slatec/dqk21.f lib/slatec/davint.f lib/slatec/dqk61.f lib/slatec/initds.f lib/slatec/pcoef.f lib/slatec/pvalue.f lib/slatec/dbsi0e.f lib/slatec/dbsk0e.f lib/slatec/dbesj1.f lib/slatec/dqk15w.f lib/slatec/dcsevl.f lib/slatec/dqk15.f lib/slatec/dqk51.f lib/slatec/dqcheb.f lib/slatec/d9b0mp.f lib/slatec/d9b1mp.f lib/slatec/dqelg.f lib/slatec/dbesi1.f lib/slatec/dbesk0.f lib/slatec/dqage.f lib/slatec/dqk41.f lib/slatec/dqc25f.f lib/slatec/dbesj0.f lib/slatec/dqawo.f lib/slatec/dgtsl.f lib/slatec/dqpsrt.f lib/slatec/.objects lib/slatec/dqk31.f qp/DFT_Vxc.F acfdt/acfdt_tot_energy.F qp_ctl/QP_apply_fit.F external_c/ct_etime.c common/pol_fit.F bz_ops/k_lattice.F pol_function/f_sum_rule.F pol_function/O_eels.F pol_function/O_driver.F pol_function/X_dipole_RIM.F pol_function/.objects pol_function/.objects_gpl coulomb/bessel_F2.F coulomb/bessel_F6.F coulomb/cutoff_cylinder.F interface/check_periodic_directions.F interface/setup.F interface/init_load.F interface/.objects interface/init.F tddft/tddft_alda_g_space.F modules/mod_logo.F modules/mod_BS.F modules/std_presets.F modules/mod_X.F modules/mod_D_lattice.F bse/K_dump_to_o_file.F bse/K_filling.F bse/K_eps_interpolate.F bse/K.F ypp/BZ_RIM.F driver/getopt.c driver/driver.c sbin/make_makefile.sh.in

  Bugs:
  - In acx_cpp.m4 wrong syntax.
  - In ct_etime.c wrong declaration of tt variable in double
    precision builds.

  Additions:
  - In configure added : --enable-msgs-comps to exapand the compilation messages
                         --enable-options-check to allow the check of the options
                                                passed to driver.c
     By using --disable-options-check it is possible to solve the
     annoying problem caused by some mpirun scripts (-p option)
  - Added DOUBLE PRECISION slatec sources
  - O_eels.F and check_periodic_directions.F. Used to allow the user
    to specify non periodic directions. In case those are given
    the polarizability is calculated by using KK transformations
    even in the TDA.

  Changes:
  - Removed different make clean*. Now only available "make clean"
    and "make clean_all". In the first case the configuration files
    are not removed and the code can be compiled without running
    configure again.
  - slatec routines used for polynomial fit replaced with
    single/double versions.

  Patch sent by: Andrea


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@359 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

