- Revision syncronization. [Andrea Marini]

  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@256 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.1.0. [Andrea Marini]

  *  pol_function/X_O_strengths.F ypp/ypp_init.F ypp/exc_properties.F ypp/exc_wf_sort_and_report.F ypp/mod_YPP.F ypp/exc_wf_gnuplot.F ypp/exc_wf_xcrysden.F ypp/ypp_init_load.F driver/ypp.h_gpl driver/ypp.h

  Additions:
  - In ypp added the possibility of reading more complex state strings
    in excitonic plot. Now a string "1 2-4 20" is parsed as well.

  Changes:
  - For back compatibility  changed the -f flag in ypp from "fixed hole" to
    "free hole". Now the "ypp -e p" creates the input for a standard
    excitonic wf. To have the periodic expression introduced in previous
    revisions use "ypp -e p -f"

  Patch sent by: Andrea


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@254 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.1.0. [Andrea Marini]

  *  interface/barriers.F io/ioBSS_diago.F ypp/exc_properties.F ypp/ypp_init.F ypp/exc_wf_sort_and_report.F ypp/mod_YPP.F ypp/ypp_init_load.F driver/ypp.h_gpl driver/ypp.h

  Bugs:
  - In barriers.F. With spin support bse runlevel was switched off

  Additions:
  - In ypp. Added the "fixed hole" option to perform a standard plot of the
    excitonic wf. Without "fixed hole" option now the hole and electron
    are imposed to have the same position (the wf is, then periodic)

  Patch sent by: Andrea


