  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@210 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.0.15. [Andrea Marini]

  *  p2s/p2s_wf.F p2s/mod_p2s.F config/Makefile.in qp/QP_driver.F qp/DFT_Vxc.F acfdt/acfdt_tot_energy.F qp_ctl/mod_QP_CTL.F common/QP_state_table_setup.F wf_and_fft/wf_load.F pol_function/X_O_transverse.F pol_function/X_O_rotate.F pol_function/O_driver.F pol_function/X_O_strengths.F interface/setup.F interface/init_load.F sc/V_Hartree.F sc/SC_driver.F tddft/tddft_alda_g_space.F io/ioBS.F io/ioBS_Fxc.F io/ioDB1.F io/ioX.F io/io_SC_components.F io/ioBSS_invert.F io/ioXXVXC.F io/ioQP.F io/load_SC_components.F io/io_header.F io/ioBSS_Haydock.F io/ioOSTNTS.F io/ioBSS_diago.F modules/mod_BS.F modules/mod_xc_functionals.F modules/std_presets.F modules/mod_SC.F modules/mod_X.F modules/mod_IO.F modules/mod_QP.F modules/.objects modules/mod_global_XC.F bse/K_driver.F bse/K_scattering_cpl.F bse/K_scattering.F bse/.objects bse/K_eh_setup.F bse/K.F ChangeLog driver/driver.c sbin/make_message.pl.in

  Bugs:
  - In p2s_wf and p2s_mod. p2s was not compiling with _P2S_EXPORT option.

  Additions:
  - _BS_CPL project (BSE coupling): in Makefile, driver.c and in src/bse/K_scattering_cpl.F (it will
    replace K_scattering when the project will be merged in the core)

  - MAJOR ADDITION ! From ver >= 3.0.15 several databases will contain in the
    header a GLOBAL_XC information.
    This information is defined in modules/mod_global_XC.F and it has been
    introduced to allow calculations in a Self-Consistent basis (HF,CHOSEX,EXX...)
    generated by the _SC project.
    In addition this GLOBAL_XC field will keep track of the "KIND" of energies
    and/or wavefunctions used. Even when a QP correction has been used.
    Analogously with the mod_xc_functional in mod_global_XC additional
    integers are introduced for the self-consistent calculations, for
    the different self-energies and scissors/stretchings ...
  - using_SC_basis is TRUE if a SC basis is to be loaded.

  Changes:
  - A P_BANDS_ORDERED logical is not stored in oscillators database to
    handle calculations in a SC basis originated from a non-local
    potential (HF, CHOSEX). This feature is still under testing.
  - QP_band_mixing -> SC_band_mixing as now non perturbative
    calculations are handled by SC_driver using a single iteration.


  Patch sent by: Andrea


  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@209 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

