  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@202 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- ACFDT tot energy can run with no call to X_em1. [Andrea Marini]

  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@201 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- Version 3.0.13 r.200. [Andrea Marini]

  *  configure spp/exc_wf_eval.F include/version.inc config/configure.ac qp/QP_driver.F qp/QP_XX_Vxc.F qp/QP_descriptions.F qp/QP_ppa_chosex.F common/QP_state_table_setup.F common/eval_G_minus_G.F pol_function/X_pre_setup.F interface/init_load.F interface/init.F coulomb/bessel_F2.F coulomb/bessel_F3.F coulomb/bessel_F4.F coulomb/bessel_F5.F coulomb/bessel_F6.F coulomb/cutoff_cylinder.F coulomb/.objects tddft/tddft_alda_g_space.F sc/SC_mute.F sc/SC_driver.F modules/std_presets.F modules/mod_SC.F modules/mod_drivers.F modules/mod_QP.F ChangeLog driver/self.h driver/self_driver.F

  Bugs:
  - Argument redefinition (like in old wf_load bug) in eval_G_minus_G
    routine (dangerous for possible memory leaks).

  Additions:
  - CHOSEX self-energy implemented. It can use only occupied bands
    or it can be used for convergence purposes using the UseEbands
    flag.
  - Added bessel function in src/coulomb/ as separate routines for
    compatibility with SP and PGf90 compilers.

  Changes:
  - Self-Consistensy: Now all local potential works (positice comparison
    with abinit results). XX, HF and CHOSEX under testing.

  - !!! NOTE !!! Command line options for "-o l"  changed in "-o c"

  Patch sent by: Andrea


