  git-svn-id: svn+ssh://qeforge.qe-forge.org/svnroot/yambo-devel/trunk@110 76a4dfbf-5f1f-0410-a543-a0282073b526

- V 3.0.8_23-03-07. [Andrea Marini]

  *  spp/BZ_RIM.F p2s/p2s_db1.F 2wf_and_fft/wf_load.F 2wf_and_fft/el_density.F 0modules/mod_electrons.F 0modules/std_presets.F 0modules/mod_BS.F 0modules/mod_X.F 0modules/mod_wave_func.F 2io/ioBS_diago.F 2io/ioX.F 2io/ioE_RIM.F 5X/X_pre_setup.F 5X/X_eh_setup.F 5X/X_os.F 5X/X_em1.F 5X/O_driver.F 5X/.objects 5X/X_checks.F 5X/X_ehg.F 7bse/K_Haydock.F 7bse/K_dump_to_o_file.F 7bse/K_filling.F 7bse/Kernel_by_V.F 7bse/.objects 7bse/K_driver.F 7bse/K_diagonalization.F 7bse/K_eh_setup.F 7bse/K_inversion.F 7bse/K_solvers.F 7bse/K.F 3qp_ctl/mod_QP_CTL.F 3qp_ctl/QP_apply_stretch.F 3qp_ctl/QP_apply_fit.F 6qp/QP_driver.F 7acfdt/acfdt_tot_energy.F 4ras/rasdriver.F

  Bugs:
  - In wf_load normalization check fixed for "few" states wf loading
  - ioBS_diago exits with error when BSS_write_eig_2_db=.FALSE. but
    BS_mat is going to be loaded
  - In O_driver X_epsilon was filled in a wrong way when the
    polarizability is calculated
  - In K.F BW_W is kept complex while the diagonal part of the kernel
    is forced real ( H_res_c=real(H_res_c) )

  Additions:
  - In interfaces (p2s, a2s) i_time_rev = 0 when nsym = 1
  - X_RIM_nkpts,BSS_uses_RIM,BS_not_const_eh_f
  - X_checks renamed in X_pre_setup
  - X_ehg renamed in X_eh_setup
  - add RIM to diagonalization BS solver (to complete)

  - BSE support for fractional occupations (finite temp. case).
    Introduced BS_not_const_eh_f and changed K_eh_setup, K_diagonalization

  Changes:
  -  Restyling of wf_load, mod_electrons, mod_wave_func, ioE_RIM, K_filling,
     K_diagonalization,K_eh_setup

  Patch sent by: Andrea


